<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
	     <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f110004969962405">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=5734&amp;mid=110004969962405">How to get Tome</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=5734&amp;mid=110004969962405#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Tue, Nov 9th 8:21 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=73102"><span id=" ">gladilie</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">8 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score:</span> Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Ok setup camp at roughly 300,200&nbsp;&nbsp;if your at an opening to a dock, I got the coordinates wrong, you will need to move to 200,300.  There is a little broken square fountain at the correct spot.  There is one rat wanderer along with a couple golem wanderers and some of the ghosts also around here. <br/><br/>When I got close I flew my eye of Alyenbomb around and found him to be a wanderer.  He wanders from the first building on the left in a path next to the fountain to the last building on the left in the next area. He goes up stairs in the back building, so total path time maybe a little under 3 minutes, although he doesn't wander the entire path every time.  He is a little short compared to other golems and is gray, not shiny metalic.  <br/><br/>Depending on your group you can figure out a strategy but don't depend on slow, root or mez to handle the golems except for poison based slow. However, I did find that some golems could be chain stunned he can't be. He has roughly 12k hp. I am certain a solo necro 66ish could take him with the pet heal AA.  <br/><br/>I moved one mob at a time up to the camp pausing often to watch for wanderers.  This zone used to be way more tricky but even if your solo or not well equiped you can take it slow and rarely get an add unlike before.<br/><br/>welcome<br/>ab<br/><br/><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Nov  9 20:23:21 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
